101. Identify, how a cookie’s value can be retrieved in a web application?

ANSWER
<?php
// Set the cookie if it's not already set
if (!isset($_COOKIE['user'])) {
    // Set a cookie named 'user' with value 'John' that expires in 1 hour
    setcookie("user", "John", time() + 3600, "/"); // "/" means it's available across the whole domain
    $cookie_message = "✅ Cookie 'user' has been set. Please reload the page to see its value.";
} else {
    // Retrieve the cookie value
    $cookie_value = $_COOKIE['user'];
    $cookie_message = "✅ Cookie 'user' is set. Value: <strong>$cookie_value</strong>";
}
?>

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>Set and Retrieve Cookie in PHP</title>
</head>
<body>

    <h2>🍪 Cookie Demo</h2>

    <p><?php echo $cookie_message; ?></p>

    <form method="post">
        <button type="submit">Reload Page</button>
    </form>

</body>
</html>

OUTPUT
Cookie Demo
Cookie 'user' has been set. Please reload the page to see its value.
Reload Page

